Review: One of the best Marvel movies I've seen in a long time but I feel like this should be rated R just for the emotional trauma lol. Sorry Mark and Julia for crying all over you on the plane multiple times :///
Just a silly and fun bank robbery woohoo!!!! Right up until the last 10 minutes :(
Great flick but that ending had me laughing for a good minute. Why did they cut it so abruptly haha

Denzel is MY MAN hahaha get it?! He really was the highlight of this for me though. Awesome, star studded cast and a great sense of atmosphere. My main qualm was that I didn't feel as invested in Russell Crowe's character until his story began to intertwine with Frank's.

A movie about change and how quickly the course of someone's life can be altered. Amazing, immersive sound design and great performances. I was itching to see more of what Ruben ended up doing music-wise especially with the foreshadowing some scenes seemed to lean into. Instead, Sound of Metal leaves things more open-ended which I still thought was a fitting end but left me wanting even more. Maybe it's just my bias as a musician haha. Would love to give Rubie a big ol HUG!

Movie: Miles Davis: Birth of the Cool

Review: 2 hours of shots of the ocean, paragliders, and a kid singing karaoke.

The one shot format really works well for Boiling Point, providing a sense of atmosphere that I don't think would be accomplished otherwise. Every performance in this is exceptional and had me equally invested in all of the different members of the restaraunt team.

Movie: Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings
Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings

Review: Minding the Gap tells a story of generational trauma and escapism. What really brings this documentary to life though, is the direction of Bing Liu. With a combination of hard hitting, upfront questions and a willingness to peel back the layers of his own life, Bing comes across something truly unique. With an exceptionally emotional and vulnerable last 20 or so minutes, Minding the Gap is an essential watch that may hopefully bring about much needed conversations and reflection in households similar to those of the 3 boys.
